t1906.text: For context, post-tax that’s $925.50 to pay rent, groceries, fuel, power, gas, internet, phone, clothing, school supplies, paying debt, medication, unexpected expenses etc... just for one fortnight. I don’t know how people are meant to survive on this at the best of times.

t1907.text: For example right now, The jobseeker payment. If someone has a partner that earns $993.50 or more (pre-tax) a F/N or $25831 pa, is ineligible for assistance. Working class/middle class Aussies are finding out how little govt. cares about those who cannot provide for themselves.
